Here are specific, actionable improvements you can make to your `practice.html` file, broken down into categories. Overall, the code is very clean, and the content is excellent, but we can elevate it with better accessibility, sturdier CSS architecture, and a more robust copy function.

### 1. HTML Semantics & Accessibility

*   **Use a `<main>` landmark:** Currently, the top-level wrapper is `<div class="container">`. Change this to `<main class="container">`. This is a crucial semantic improvement that allows screen readers to navigate directly to your primary content.
*   **Add ARIA labels to copy buttons:** The text "copy" is okay, but `aria-label="Copy code to clipboard"` provides better context for screen readers.
*   **Keyboard Focus Styles:** The native `<summary>` and your custom `.copy-btn` rely on default browser focus rings. It's best to explicitly style `:focus-visible` so keyboard navigators know exactly where they are.

```css
/* Add explicit focus states */
.accordion summary:focus-visible,
.copy-btn:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid var(--accent);
  outline-offset: 2px;
  border-radius: 4px;
}
```

### 2. CSS Architecture & UI Tweaks

*   **Remove `!important` flags:** Using `!important` to override Prism.js defaults is a code smell and can make future maintenance frustrating. Instead, target Prism's specific class selector to increase your CSS specificity.
*   **Prevent Text Overlap:** If a code block has long lines that scroll horizontally, the text will currently slide underneath your absolute-positioned `.copy-btn`, making the end of the line hard to read. Adding extra `padding-right` fixes this.

```css
/* Replace your .accordion-body pre rule with this: */
.accordion-body pre[class*="language-"] {
  margin: 0;
  border-radius: 0;
  background: #141414;
  font-size: 0.82rem;
  line-height: 1.65;
  /* Notice the 60px right padding to make room for the copy button */
  padding: 20px 60px 20px 22px; 
  overflow-x: auto;
}

.accordion-body pre[class*="language-"] code {
  font-family: var(--font-mono);
}
```

### 3. JavaScript Robustness

*   **Use `.textContent` over `.innerText`:** In your copy function, you are using `code.innerText`. Because `innerText` respects CSS (like `text-transform` or `display: none`) and triggers a browser layout recalculation, it's generally safer and faster to use `.textContent` for grabbing raw code blocks.
*   **Handle Clipboard Errors:** The `navigator.clipboard` API can throw errors if permissions are denied or if the file isn't being served over a secure context (HTTPS/localhost). Wrapping it in a `try/catch` is best practice.

```javascript
document.querySelectorAll('.copy-btn').forEach(btn => {
  btn.addEventListener('click', async () => {
    // Use textContent instead of innerText
    const code = btn.closest('.accordion-body').querySelector('code').textContent;

    try {
      await navigator.clipboard.writeText(code);
      btn.textContent = 'copied!';
      btn.classList.add('copied');
    } catch (err) {
      btn.textContent = 'error';
      console.error('Failed to copy text: ', err);
    }

    setTimeout(() => { 
      btn.textContent = 'copy'; 
      btn.classList.remove('copied'); 
    }, 1500);
  });
});
```

### 4. Optional Enhancements

*   **Responsive Adjustments:** On mobile screens, `20px` of padding inside the `<pre>` block wastes valuable horizontal space. Consider adding a media query to shrink this:
    ```css
    @media (max-width: 600px) {
      .accordion-body pre[class*="language-"] {
        padding: 16px 50px 16px 16px;
      }
      body {
        padding: 20px 10px 40px;
      }
    }
    ```
*   **Exclusive Accordion (Accordion Group):** If you want to automatically close other sections when opening a new one, you can use the relatively new HTML `name` attribute on the `<details>` tags. Adding `name="js-syntax"` to all JavaScript `<details>` tags will group them natively without needing JS.
    ```html
    <details class="accordion" name="js-practice">
       <summary>Arrow Functions &amp; Closures</summary>
       <!-- ... -->
    </details>
    <details class="accordion" name="js-practice">
       <summary>Destructuring &amp; Spread</summary>
       <!-- ... -->
    </details>
    ```

